# GitHub App Configuration
# 
# HOW TO GET THESE VALUES:
# 1. Create a GitHub App at: https://github.com/settings/apps/new
# 2. After creating the app, you'll find the App ID on the app settings page
# 3. Set a webhook secret when creating the app (generate one with: openssl rand -hex 20)
# 4. Copy both values here
#
# Detailed instructions: See SETUP.md for step-by-step guide

# The App ID from your GitHub App
# Where to find: GitHub Settings → Developer settings → GitHub Apps → Your App → "App ID" field at the top
GH_APP_ID=

# The webhook secret you set when creating your GitHub App
# Where to find: You set this yourself during app creation in the "Webhook secret" field
# Generate a new one with: openssl rand -hex 20
# Note: This must match the webhook secret configured in your GitHub App settings
GH_WEBHOOK_SECRET=

# IMPORTANT: Setup Instructions
# 1. Copy this file to .env: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Fill in GH_APP_ID and GH_WEBHOOK_SECRET above
# 3. Generate a private key from your GitHub App settings
# 4. Download the .pem file and save it as 'private-key.pem' in this directory (apps/bot/)
# 5. The .gitignore is already configured to ignore *.pem and .env files
#
# For detailed setup instructions, see SETUP.md
